outputs:
{"answer": "To allow an AI to read a static local configuration file, the server developer can use the "Resource registration" or "Tool registration" features. However, a more direct and relevant approach would be to define a resource endpoint for the configuration file.

In MCP, resources are defined as endpoints that provide access to external data sources. A server developer can register a resource using an SDK helper function, specifying the type of resource (e.g., file) and its location on the local file system. This enables clients to retrieve the configuration file contents.

To make this work securely, the server should be configured to interact only with one designated directory, as mentioned in the context you provided. By registering a resource endpoint for the configuration file within this isolated directory, the developer can ensure that the AI has controlled access to the necessary data while maintaining system security and stability.", "context": "MCP_landscape_security_threats.pdf p30 | the_model_context_protocol.pdf p13 | agent_engineering_enterprise.pdf p66 | the_model_context_protocol.pdf p26 | the_model_context_protocol.pdf p5 | MCP_landscape_security_threats.pdf p8 | agent_engineering_enterprise.pdf p68"}

