{"answer": "Based on the provided context, if a user wants an AI to be able to read a static local configuration file, the server developer should use the "sandbox" enforcement during dynamic operations. 

This is because the sandbox introduced during deployment limits file access to a predefined scope, which in this case can include the designated directory where the static local configuration file resides. By maintaining active sandbox enforcement during execution, even if an error occurs, the server's resource boundaries are confined within the controlled environment, preventing unnecessary exposure of system paths.

In other words, the developer should ensure that the AI is operating within a restricted account and access permissions to read only the designated directory where the configuration file is stored.", "context": "MCP_landscape_security_threats.pdf p30 | MCP_landscape_security_threats.pdf p30 | MCP_landscape_security_threats.pdf p8"}

