outputs:
{"answer": "Based on the context, here is a description of the client-server handshake process:

When an MCP connection is first initialized, the client sends an "initialize" request to the server, advertising its capabilities and the protocol version it supports. The server then replies with an "initialize result", confirming the protocol version to be used and declaring its own connection process.

This handshake process initiates the communication between the client and server, allowing them to negotiate the protocol version, capability negotiation, and session state management (such as timeouts, interruptions, and reconnections).", "context": "the_model_context_protocol.pdf p15 | agent_engineering_enterprise.pdf p83 | the_model_context_protocol.pdf p12 | MCP_landscape_security_threats.pdf p6 | the_model_context_protocol.pdf p17"}

